The paper presents a data structure for handling edge deletions and answering queries related to biconnectivity in graphs. This suggests that the paper belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of nested r-divisions, which are a type of geometric partitioning, indicating a possible connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the applicability of the data structure to planar graphs and other minor-free graphs, which suggests a potential connection to algorithms and complexity (cs.SI) as these classes of graphs are often studied in the context of algorithmic problems.
